OL,3,CWhy cutting disability benefits will
OL,4,Cbe a nightmare for the government
OL,6,FThe proposed reforms relate to the
OL,7,FWork Capability Assessment (WCA) that
OL,8,Fcategorises people on Universal Credit
OL,9,Finto three groups: those who are found
OL,10,Fto be fine for work and so must
OL,11,F"intensively" search for it; those who
OL,12,Fare judged to be able to seek work,
OL,13,Fbut whose health issues may mean they
OL,14,Fstruggle with a job itself; and those
OL,15,Fwho are too disabled or unwell to work
OL,16,Fat all. The third group receive an
OL,17,Fextra #416 a month.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
