OL,3,CWhy cutting disability benefits will
OL,4,Cbe a nightmare for the government
OL,6,FThe eye-watering bill for these
OL,7,Fbenefits led the Conservatives to
OL,8,Fpropose changing the tests - in a way
OL,9,Fthat would move people down, out of
OL,10,Fthe most severe group.
OL,12,FMel Stride argued that it was all
OL,13,Fabout supporting people into work. But
OL,14,Fwas it? Not according to the Office
OL,15,Ffor Budget Responsibility whose
OL,16,Fforecasts about the impact of the
OL,17,Fpolicy cast serious doubt over the
OL,18,Fmotive.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
