OL,3,CWhy cutting disability benefits will
OL,4,Cbe a nightmare for the government
OL,6,FThey believe that only 15,400 more
OL,7,Fpeople will move into employment over
OL,8,Fthe same period. No wonder the policy
OL,9,Fsaves money, given that it seems to
OL,10,Flargely amount to a massive cut in
OL,11,Fpeoples' benefits.
OL,13,FThese figures were seen as so shocking
OL,14,Fthey led to a legal challenge by
OL,15,Fdisability campaigner Ellen Clifford
OL,16,Fand, as mentioned, the court agreed
OL,17,Fthat the consultation was unlawful.
OL,18,FHer basic argument was that the
OL,19,Fgovernment's main motive was saving
OL,20,Fmoney and not boosting employment, and
OL,21,Fthe judge agreed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
