OL,3,CWhy cutting disability benefits will
OL,4,Cbe a nightmare for the government
OL,6,FLast night on ITV's Peston, Kendall
OL,7,Fagreed that the consultation was a
OL,8,Fmess and that her government would
OL,9,Fstart again. So did she accept that
OL,10,Fthe #3 billion savings would also
OL,11,Fvanish? No, she insisted the
OL,12,Fgovernment was committed to it,
OL,13,Freferring to helping job centres get
OL,14,Fpeople into work.
OL,16,FNo one would disagree that those who
OL,17,Fcan work, should be supported to do
OL,18,Fso, but how can the government commit
OL,19,Fto such massive savings when the
OL,20,Fproposals on which they were based
OL,21,Fhave crumbled?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
